dct_title_s: Illinois-Indiana-Kentucky, New Haven quadrangle [1966 reprint with vegetation]
dct_description_sm: United States, Department of the Interior, Geological Survey , State of Illinois, Department of Registration and Education, Geological Survey Division , State of Kentucky, represented by the Department of Mines and Minerals , H. M. Wilson, geographer , Chas. E. Cooke, in charge of section , topography by W. J. Lloyd and L. Scott Smith. Filing title: New Haven, Ill.-Ind.-Ky., 1949. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Contour interval 20 feet. Shows portions of Gallatin and White counties, Illinois, Posey County, Indiana, and Union County, Kentucky. Surveyed in 1905. "Culture revised in part, 1938 and 1949." Reprinted 1966. Some copies show forest areas colored green. "W3745--N8800/15."
Dimensions: 45 x 42 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:62,500
dct_creator_sm: Lloyd, W. J. (Topographer); Smith, L. Scott; Illinois State Geological Survey; Wilson, Herbert M. (Herbert Michael), 1860-1920; Ellis, J. R. (Topographer); Cooke, Chas. E. (Charles E.); Geological Survey (U.S.); Kentucky. Department of Mines and Minerals
